-- Bugs Fixed and Ready For Relase 36
Added: Tooltips over tanks
Added: Decimal point on tank evelevation/rotation angles
Added: Depth buffer size can be set in config
Added: Menu items + drop down lists change color when available (mouse over)
Added: Can now kick computer players (from server dialog)
Added: Can now add computer players (from server dialog)
Added: Can set number of sprites and bilboards
Added: Talk text now has tank state appended to it (dead, pending)
Added: Buy dialog shows all available weapons
Added: Buy dialog order and position don't change after buy
Added: Tank choice dialog shows many more tanks
Added: Tanks placed into catagories to make for easier choosing
Added: MilkShape model support (including alpha maps)
Added: Keys are defined and can be configured via XML file (keys.xml)
Added: Resouces can be enabled and disabled in the resource file 
Added: Specified landscape textures to be disabled
Added: Weapons are defined and can be configured via XML file (accessories.xml)
Added: Bots (AIs) are defined and can be configured via XML file (tankai.xml)
Added: Auto aim (A key), points tank to a position on the landscape
Added: Server password functionality
Added: Tank has multiple falling contact points (stops tank being burried when falling)
Added: Weapon icons in the buy/sell dialogs
Added: Start of Hexidecimal support
Added: Cross platform server browsing
Added: Aiming cross hair can be seen from above
Added: Can turn off player triangles, sight, names and health bars
Added: Tank models can have different turret and gun pivot points
Added: Tank models can contain multiple gun and turret objects
Added: New version of ODE physics engine used
Added: Missiles now have a model and not just a photon torpedo
Added: Missile models can be configured on a per weapon basis
Added: Coms message and state logging
Added: Client can log to file
Added: Plan dialogs now updated when landscape removed
Added: Detail texture added to landscape (for cards that support it)
Added: Waves around island is blended and does not look so pixelated
Added: The water around the island is lighter and looks shallow
Added: Water texture added to water (on top of the existing reflection) (for cards that support it)
Added: Simultaneous and sequential game modes are available for both online and single player
Added: Player ordering can be specified for sequential game modes
Added: Landscape width can be set (smaller landscapes only)
Added: Better scroll bar controls
Added: Widgets are all now rounded
Added: Mushroom clouds for nukes
Added: MOTD and rules displayed when player connects
Added: Dirt or water cloud for explosions
Added: Start of trees for landscape
Added: All server<->client coms message are compressed
Added: Player connects before choosing tank + name
Added: Network players now wait for more players in the game (not the connection dialog)
Added: Option to not limit the shot power according to health
Added: Wrap around wall option
Added: Money can be awarded for hits as well as kills
Added: New camera angle shows the final position of shots and killed tanks
Added: Different scoring modes (winner chosen in different ways)
Added: Team Play
Added: Team auto ballancing
Added: can change team, tank and name during game

Fixed: Tank bounding boxes can still cause collisions when tank is dead
Fixed: Random windows crashes, increased stack size to stop ODE from running out of stack
Fixed: Tanks do not start right at the landscape edge
Fixed: Applied http://wwwra.informatik.uni-rostock.de/~waschk/Scorched3D-35-gcc3.3.patch
Fixed: Landscape explosions are much faster
Fixed: Text drawn outside dialogs (help and connect dialogs)
Fixed: Player name will always fit on score dialog
Fixed: can set number arguments via the console
Fixed: Reduced bilboards and sprites used
Fixed: SHFT/CTRL keys wrong way round in README
Fixed: Auto defense dialog shown for other players
Fixed: +/- keys do not work on key pad
Fixed: Auto defense dialog+bug dialog can be shown multiple times for same player
Fixed: Computer players say stuff when killed
Fixed: Player/Quit menu option does not work in single player mode
Fixed: Moved timer, so talk text is not in the way
Fixed: Texturing of Milkshape models (Each texture must be a 256x256 bmp)

